The paper discusses the problem of interpreting natural language sentences, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of AI systems to solve this problem, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The SP System, which is the focus of the paper, is a machine learning model, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for appropriate knowledge of syntax and semantics, which suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for the SP System to learn the knowledge needed for interpreting Winograd Schemas, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be a relevant sub-category.
